BIREME/EIH launches new version of e-BlueInfo				




Press Release – PAHO/WHO, through the Latin American and Caribbean Center on Health Sciences Information, which is part of the Department of Evidence and Intelligence for Action in Health (BIREME/EIH) and the PAHO offices in Brazil, El Salvador, Guatemala and Peru, invites to participate virtually at the launch of the e-BlueInfo version 2.0 application.



e-BlueInfo is an application that places in the hand of health professionals reliable information, updated and selected by experts from the Ministries of Health and the countries’ educational and research institutions. It also includes PAHO/WHO Guidelines. 



Date: Tuesday, March 30, 2021 



Time: 2:00 pm-3:30 pm (GMT -3)  



link: https://paho-org.zoom.us/webinar/register/WN_yno6qpWdS1iadnsgEOtnfw



The event will feature simultaneous interpretation from Spanish to Portuguese and English.



Sign up right now!



Agenda:



Moderator: Dr Diego González. Director of BIREME



Opening – Dr. Jarbas Barbosa. Assistant Director of PAHO/WHO.



Resilience of health systems: a priority for the Americas. Dr. James Fitzgerald. Director of the Department of Health Systems and Services. HSS/PAHO/WHO. 



e-BlueInfo 2.0 – what’s new? – Mr. Renato Murasaki. Information Technology Manager. BIREME/PAHO/WHO.



Remarks from participant countries:



Dr. Raphael Câmara Medeiros Parente, Secretary of Primary Health Care. Brazilian Ministry of Health.Dr. Xochitl Sandoval, Director of the National Health Institute. Ministry of Health of El Salvador.Dr. Edwin Eduardo Montúfar Velarde, Vice-Minister of Primary Care. Guatemalan Ministry of Public Health and Social Assistance.  Dr. Fernando Carbone Campoverde, Advisor to the Ministerial Office of the Peruvian Ministry of Health.   



Closing remarks. Dr. Sebastián García Saisó. Director of the Department of Evidence and Intelligence for Action in Health. EIH/PAHO/WHO.